EBOLA HEMORRHAGIC FEVER - CONGO REPUBLIC (03)
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Wed 25 May 2005
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: World Health Organization (WHO), CSR, Disease Outbreak News,
Wed 25 May 2005 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2005_05_25/en/index.html>

Republic of Congo: Ebola hemorrhagic fever outbreak - WHO update; 25 May 2005
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
As of 24 May 2005, a total of 12 cases (one laboratory-confirmed and
11 epidemiologically linked), including 9 deaths, has been reported
in Etoumbi and Mbomo in Cuvette Ouest Region. The additional case is
a contact from Etoumbi [see ProMED-mail post entitled "Undiagnosed
deaths - Congo Rep. (04): Ebola confirmed 20050518.1358" or previous
WHO report at
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2005_05_18/en/index.html>.
- Mod.CP]
71 contacts are being monitored in Etoumbi (62) and Mbomo (9).
The Ministry of Health and the WHO Regional Office for Africa are
continuing to follow contacts and raise awareness about the disease
among the population in the affected districts.
